00:00:07.400 --> 00:00:09.400
This is the recipe for Rendang Tok.

00:00:10.080 --> 00:00:12.080
A popular dish during the Eid Festivals.

00:00:12.080 --> 00:00:13.340
The ingredients needed

00:00:13.640 --> 00:00:15.640
500g beef (3 inch slices)

00:00:15.980 --> 00:00:17.980
2 cups coconut milk

00:00:18.160 --> 00:00:20.160
3 tablespoon kerisik

00:00:20.400 --> 00:00:22.400
2 tablespoon brown sugar

00:00:23.220 --> 00:00:25.220
2 pieces asam gelugor

00:00:25.220 --> 00:00:26.860
2 pieces turmeric leaves

00:00:27.400 --> 00:00:29.400
and salt to taste.

00:00:29.560 --> 00:00:31.560
Ingredients to blend

00:00:31.560 --> 00:00:32.280
15 pieces dried chili

00:00:32.880 --> 00:00:34.880
10 pieces shallots

00:00:34.980 --> 00:00:36.980
2 cloves garlic

00:00:36.980 --> 00:00:38.720
3 stalks lemongrass

00:00:39.280 --> 00:00:41.280
1 inch ginger

00:00:42.340 --> 00:00:44.340
1 inch galangal

00:00:44.920 --> 00:00:46.920
1 tablespoon coriander

00:00:47.300 --> 00:00:49.300
1 teaspoon cumin

00:00:51.920 --> 00:00:53.920
1 teaspoon black pepper

00:00:55.300 --> 00:00:57.300
2 pieces mace flower and 5 pieces clove

00:00:57.860 --> 00:00:59.860
3 cups water

00:00:59.860 --> 00:01:01.000
The method,

00:01:03.380 --> 00:01:11.680
Blend (dry) the coriander, black pepper, cumin, mase flower and cloves until it turns to powder.

00:01:17.680 --> 00:01:26.180
Then blend the dry chillies with shallots, lemongrass, garlic, galangal and ginger with some water.

00:01:41.520 --> 00:01:42.840
Blend until it turns to paste.

00:01:49.600 --> 00:01:55.540
In a wok, pour in the dry and wet blended ingredients with the brown sugar and beef.

00:02:06.480 --> 00:02:07.460
Mix well.

00:02:11.580 --> 00:02:17.260
Add in the coconut milk and cook on low heat until it thickens and oil starts to rise.

00:02:23.880 --> 00:02:28.620
Once thick, add in the asam keping, kerisik and salt.

00:02:36.020 --> 00:02:38.300
Mix until well incorporated.

00:02:39.600 --> 00:02:42.760
Thinly slice the turmeric leaves and add it into the rendang.

00:02:56.920 --> 00:03:01.340
Mix well and it is ready to be served with lemang!

